dct_description_sm: This polygon data layer represents historic urban growth for South Eastern Wisconsin in 2004. The dataset was originally published by the Southeastern Wisconsin Regional Planning Commission (SEWRPC) on August 26, 2004.[This data set contains polygon features showing the growth of urban areas in the seven-county Southeastern Wisconsin Region. The polygon features were digitized from delineations prepared from aerial photographs, historical maps and records, and other reference materials. The data set contains the approximated boundaries of urbanized development for selected years from 1850 to 1995. The historic urban growth polygons are identified according to year of urban development.]
